Description:
WHAT A CHARMER !!!
This seaside California Bungalow needs some love but has so much potential and if brought back to its original glory would be the perfect period home. Offering so much character, charm and warmth and with a block size of 695 sq.m. Featuring the following:
- Double door entry
- Seperate living area with bay window
- Ceiling rose
- Good sized older kitchen
- Dining area
- 3 bedrooms - master spacious size
Additional features -
- High ceilings
- Wide back deck
- Timber floors
- Dado panelling
- Fenced back yard
Go for walks along the beach or take the dog for a walk through the Gurdies bush. Only minutes away from small group of shops which has permanent doctor, chemist, ambulance depot, newsagency, cafes and also you have the local wineries. The v-line bus stop is metres away so great for commuting to Dandenong. Major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx. 30 mins and easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway.
This property is being sold as is!!!! What you see is what you get!!!!!

Country family living on 997sqm
Proudly positioned amongst the tranquil setting situates this young 34 square JG King "steel frame" home on a huge 997sqm approx. parcel of land. The modern finishes and dynamic floorplan will be sure to impress, with room for all the family to enjoy.
- Two living rooms as well as theatre room and kid's retreat
- Modern kitchen featuring walk in pantry

Further complimenting this outstanding home is the fantastic location, within walking distance to all the amenities and facilities the village has to offer including shops, Brewery, Lang Lang Primary School, Child Care Centre, public transport plus easy access to Western Port Hwy and other major road arterials.

Description:
VENDOR SAYS SELL
HILL VIEW HAVEN !!! An enchanting and unique A-frame cottage oozing charm and plenty of character. The minute you arrive at the property the inviting façade entices you to see what the inside offers - and it only gets better!
Interior spaces honour the gorgeous timber polished floors throughout and exposed beams and fresh natural tones. The home boasts open plan living, dining area and fully equipped modern kitchen and the luxury of a butlers pantry which is great for hiding those dishes and mess when entertaining guests. There is a nook/office area and a family bathroom with a free standing bath, shower and also laundry area. The 2nd level features a powder room which is complemented by 2 bedrooms , master having french doors to balcony which has safety laminated glass so you can just settle back have a wine and take in the surrounds and the variety of colourful birds. A spiral staircase takes you to the attic which is equipped with 2 beds and split-system air conditioning and also offers some glimpses of bay is ideal for teenagers retreat. A carport, fully fenced backyard, circular driveway and paved path are just more the property has on offer. You must inspect to truly appreciate. Dont let this rare opportunity pass by. Stroll to the cafes and shops or visit the local wineries. Major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx. 25 mins and easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway.

Description:
Large Allotment - Final Stage of Eastern Shores
Lot 29 Yaringa Close, 1498m2
Eastern Shores Estate last and FINAL land release is underway with Titles expected early-mid 2018.
The land enjoys views towards the sea and the woodland nature reserve next to the estate. Land sizes vary and the land whilst mostly flat has some elevated lots which will capture views. This is the final stage of land release in Grantville at present so get in early to secure your lot. Eastern Shores is located minutes stroll away from all the shops and services in Grantville which include a Post Office, Newsagency, Council Offices, Medical Centre, Ambulance station and Chemist. There are a number of Cafes and fast food outlets and a Bakery. Grantville is approx. 20 mins from San Remo, 30 mins from Wonthaggi and Cowes and approx. 35 mins from Cranbourne and Pakenham. There is an excellent new Early Childhood campus beside the popular Bass Valley Primary School and there are multiple Secondary School options in the locality. A V- Line Bus runs regularly to Melbourne and beyond into Gippsland. The township is growing rapidly but land is running out just as fast!
Deposit of $500 is due upon signing contracts with the balance of 10% deposit within 21 days. The balance will be due within 14 days of the Titles being issued by the Land Titles office.
Contact Liz Leahy for more information on 0487 022 099

Description:
COASTAL LIFESTYLE - PRICED TO SELL!
This charming beachside 3 bedroom hardi-plank cottage of approx. 15 squares has a shared ENS to Master & 2nd bedroom with WIR's to both, and an additional 3rd BDRM is serviced by the family bathroom (inc bath, shower & vanity) adjacent to the WC & large laundry.
The spacious open plan meals, family & lounge have high ceilings, with ornate cornices & large windows which provide a light & airy interior capturing 'Bay Glimpes' making it a tranquil place to relax beside the 'Ultimate' wood heater in Winter, or during the Summer months; open the glass sliding door to let the outside in.
Solar Panels attached to the garage provide low cost electricity bills to the ‘Man Cave’.
Cooking will be a pleasure in the crisp clean Kitchen with shiny white two pack pantry & cabinetry with laminate counter-tops, near new gas stove, along with a range-hood and Dishwasher.
The home is enhanced by a large Colorbond powered garage for 2 cars with a concrete floor & auto roller door. The driveway provides additional off-street parking for 2-4 cars/boat/caravan or trade vehicle/s making this property instantly appealing to many buyers.
This 'beach side beauty' on a 568m2 block has a low maintenance garden incl. veggie beds & will give you a fantastic lifestyle with the Beach accessible via a path just outside your front door.
It's also walking distance to the township with several cafes, Aust Post, Bendigo Bank, Pharmacy, Medical Centre & Pathology, Laundromat, Chicken Shop, Fish & Chips, Pizza & Pasta, BP Service Station, Liquor Outlet, Transaction Centre, and V-line Bus Stop to Wonthaggi, Dandenong or Melbourne. Grantville is 20 minutes drive to San Remo or 30 minutes to Wonthaggi, 35 minutes to Pakenham, 40 minutes to Cranbourne and 45 minutes to Fountain Gate.
This home represents a great opportunity & value for money buying, with your chance to own a property within a tightly held pocket. The Seller genuinely wants to sell the property, so call me to book your private inspection, as I don't expect this home to last long!
**Please note: I am a Mobile Agent working for the Max Brown Real Estate Group based in Croydon, although I operate from a local office; and inspections can be arranged easily.

Description:
Make your move to Bass:-34 Hade Avenue, Bass
Planning Zone: Township Zone 1349 sq meters.
Suitable for residential or commercial development (STCA).
Nestled in the idyllic township of Bass, this block of land is approx. 1349 sqm and just off the Bass Highway. It will suit a family business or a couple/family looking to start a new lifestyle with a rural aspect. Located in close proximity to beaches, Phillip Island and schools including Newhaven College. The land is also close to the George Bass Hotel and is a short distance from the general store, post office, community centre and local sporting grounds.
The V/Line bus services stop in town several times a day providing easy access to other facilities in the Bass Coast region. This includes the Koo Wee Rup main terminal which has express buses to Melbourne.

Description:
LARGE COASTAL BLOCK WITH RURAL VIEWS!!!
Tenby Point is a unique location which gives the feel of privacy, tranquillity and native setting. This slightly undulating block of approx. 1, 298 sq.m. has a couple of established trees and a gorgeous rural outlook.
Take a stroll to the foreshore which is full of character and popular for fishing from the rocks. Build your ideal holiday or permanent home and enjoy the wildlife, beautiful birds and surrounds.
Bring the boat as there is a 24 hour boat ramp only minutes away, plus general store, tennis courts, community hall, lawn bowls and v-line/school bus stop. This property is ideal for those who want to have room for the kids to play or those who want a spacious block and rural living. Phillip Island and major shopping centre approx. 25 mins and easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway.

Description:
A HIDDEN TREASURE ON A GREAT BLOCK!
Such a beautifully presented home at the top of the seaside town of Pioneer Bay, this is the property you have been searching for!
Situated in an elevated position, this property boasts a large alotment of approximately 748 square metres. Entering via the newly refurbished front deck which has ample space for entertaining, and looks over the large front gardens and out to Westernport Bay beyond.
The home has been renovated throughout and includes all new floor coverings, window furnishings, updated fittings to the kitchen, stainless steel appliances and reverse cycle unit. Offering a large open plan kitchen with plenty of bench space and a separate butlers pantry. This opens out to the meals area and living room which includes wood heating and comfort of new carpet. All three bedrooms are a good size and are serviced by an updated main bathroom. The laundry is well equipped and houses the hot water service in what can be used as a drying cupboard.
This property captures views out to the water and out the garden, whilst also having good screening from the gravel road, paling fence and mature trees. The property is fully fenced and allows separate areas from the front yard to the back allowing space for the kids and the pets. A large single garage and garden shed complete this package.
Only 5 minutes from the Grantville township, this property is one for your inspection list. Contact the friendly team at Alex Scott & Staff Bass Valley today to arrange your inspection.

Description:
CLOSE TO THE SHOPS AND CAFES!!!
Set back on the block this beachside home comprises open plan living with floating floor, coonara woodheater, ceiling fan, air cooler, meals area and new country style kitchen with island bench and 5 burner stainless steel stove, 3 bedrooms all with new carpet , 2 having built-in-robes, master with ceiling fan, older style bathroom and laundry. Step outside to the undercover outdoor area which has a fish pond , there is a garden shed and another concreted area for bbq entertaining. The property backs onto rural land which offers a peaceful setting. Bring down the caravan and boat as the front yard has plenty of room and the garage is a long single which accommodates 2 vehicles comfortably. The property is currently rented on a month to month basis. Ideal holiday home/permanent or rental investment. Walk to the group of shops which includes a permanent doctor, chemist, ambulance depot, bank and cafes or stroll down to the foreshore. Grantville is a quaint coastal town approx. 110kms to the CBD. Major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx. 25 mins.

POTENTIAL PLUS

Upon entry into the house you are welcomed by a light filled sun-room with large windows and a very bright and spacious living area. The kitchen features a new tiled splash-back and a generous meals area. There are two bedrooms to the home, one with a full wall of built in robes. Description:
DELIGHTFUL WATERFRONT OPPORTUNITY
Here is a fabulous opportunity to enter the waterfront market of the tightly held Corinella foreshore. Being offered for the first time since 1989, this well established family home is situated on a double block of approximately 1025 square metres.
The home is well built and provides two large living zones, both with big windows out to the front, room for lounges and dining and both having wood heating. The original kitchen is still in place and offers ample room for entertaining. Stepping down the central hallway is the large laundry with door to the rear and ample storage, separate toilet, main bathroom with spa bath and separate shower. Three good sized bedrooms service the home and have lovely outlooks to the foreshore and gardens.
This property does not disappoint, with lovely outlooks on the grounds as well as out to Westernport. Externally this home offers mature fruit trees, garden beds and paths, along with a garden shed, pond, huge boat shed with plenty of room for the workshop, as well as a large double carport and off street parking.
Don't miss your opportunity, contact the team at Alex Scott & Staff Bass Valley today to arrange your inspection!
